  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\n1. When opened emoji popup is opened, related icon should be highlighted\r\n2. Emoji popup close policy should be consistent with other popups - clicking on input should not close the popup\r\n\r\nThe reason of those inconsistencies is the fact that StatusEmojiPopup comes from AppMain. Other popups are instantiated directly in StatusChatInput.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Go to any chat.\r\n2. Open emoji popup\r\n3. Click on input field\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n1. Opened emoji should result in highlighted emoji icon\r\n2. Clicking on input field should not close the popup\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n1. Opened emoji is not reflected by the emoji icon\r\n2. Clicking on input field closes the popup\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20650004/185601724-748fdf2c-f765-4e90-a9f0-e3a4c108af89.mp4\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version:\r\n- Operating System: Ubuntu\r\n\r\n",
